examples.en: They tightened the noose around his neck.
The rope tightened around his body.
She tightened her hold on the handle.
He tightened the screw with one last turn.
His mouth tightened into a thin, angry line.
He tightened his hold, refusing to let her go.
The general opinion among police officers was that the law should be tightened.
Rebel forces have tightened their hold on the capital.
She tightened the mainsail while holding the course (=travelling in the same direction as planned).
